      "text": "An American artist glass artist studied at the Venini glass studio in Venice, Italy in 1968. In the 20th century they allowed a artist from another country learn this century long secret. Now he is known world wide for his beautiful blown glass. His name is Dale Chihuly, from Seattle, Washington",
      "likeCount": 0,
      "publishedAt": "2026-07-11T04:01:58Z",
      "replyCount": 1,
      "replies": [
        {
          "id": "UgyFTGb_cdZUM47uc7B4AaABAg.AZ6Mxvlfde6AZ6YKsJZtJW",
          "author": "@WhereonEarth4K",
          "authorImage": "https://yt3.ggpht.com/eGYI9iH4DF7Eb8QJYMMO2qNL_ls-4aNbWgY0tHLbCMrP4phySA3gN8SnhWB02TzySTEBGRXAIg=s48-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj",
          "text": "The Venini connection — Chihuly carrying that Murano lineage back to Seattle — is one of the quietest ways Venice's craft tradition spread across the world. Thank you for watching. 🌿",
          "likeCount": 0,
          "publishedAt": "2026-07-11T05:41:22Z"
        }
      ]
